description:
King Crimson
Central Park, NYC
June 25, 1973

Lineage: 16mm Film --&gt; DVD --&gt; You
Direct transfer, professionally done with no editing, colour correction, etc.
What you see is what the film actually looks like.

The setlist is short but super-sweet:

Easy Money--&gt;
Improv


This snippet has circulated among Crimso collectors for years, but never in this quality.
I got it from a friend who owns the actual film. Following many years of me pestering him,
he finally got around to getting the transfer done.
Please share this freely and circulate it as much as possible in the hopes that perhaps
the forces of evil will be thwarted. We can only hope that this might inspire the powers
that be to commercially release the entire show. Snippets of the Larks\&amp;#039; Tongues I
from this show were used for the 1973 television promo for the album\&amp;#039;s initial realease,
so one could assume (albeit a fantasy) that the entire set was filmed and is in the
can somewhere. Many thanks to all who stay on to help seed.

